able energy projects.LiNeBrEaKAbout 2,000 people attended the ball at Donald W. Reynolds Center for American Art and Portraiture in downtown Washington. 		ENVIRONMENT and NATURAL RESOURCES (93%); ENVIRONMENTALISM (90%); US PRESIDENTS (91%); ENERGY and ENVIRONMENT (90%); ENVIRONMENTAL and WILDLIFE ORGANIZATIONS (90%); PUBLIC POLICY (90%); AIR QUALITY REGULATION (89%); RENEWABLE ENERGY (89%); EMISSIONS (78%); ENERGY DEVELOPMENT PROGRAMS (78%); OBAMA'S FIRST 100 DAYS (78%); GLOBAL WARMING (76%); ENVIRONMENTAL DEPARTMENTS (73%); CELEBRITIES (73%); US ENVIRONMENTAL LAW (73%); ART and ARTISTS (68%); NOBEL PRIZES (53%)  		LEAGUE OF CONSERVATION VOTERS (56%); US ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION AGENCY (55%); COUNCIL ON ENVIRONMENTAL QUALITY (55%)  	BARACK OBAMA (94%); AL GORE (92%); GEORGE W BUSH (92%)  	EARTH (79%) UNITED STATES (97%)  	January 23, 2009  	ENGLISH  			Newspaper  	2009 The Salt Lake Tribune All Rights Reserved  	By Dina Cappiello The Associated Press  															
