n $20 billion in renewable energy tax cuts and a tax credit for research and development on energy conservation, energy efficiency and renewable energy. It also includes a multiyear extension of the renewable energy production tax credit for wind, hydropower, geothermal and bioenergy.LiNeBrEaKIn the long run, the efforts to combat climate change and global warming should lead to more work on renewable energy projects and other initiatives, Neumaier said, even if the short-term outlook is less certain.LiNeBrEaKNeumaier said the company's conservative financial position also should help EandE weather the economic crisis. The company has $14 million in cash and only a little more than $2 million in debt.LiNeBrEaKThe company got even stronger in the first quarter, with profits almost tripling. The company also bought back 197,000 shares of its stock from a free-falling hedge fund, Tontine Associates, that needed to sell its shares in August, a move that is expected to add to EandE's earnings per share.LiNeBrEaK"We've been operating pretty well in this financial crisis," Neumaier said.LiNeBrEaKdrobinson@buffnews.com		ENVIRONMENT and NATURAL RESOURCES (90%); ENERGY and ENVIRONMENT (90%); ENVIRONMENTAL INDUSTRY (90%); EMISSIONS (89%); ENERGY DEVELOPMENT PROGRAMS (89%); RENEWABLE ENERGY (89%); CLIMATE CHANGE (89%); ELECTRIC POWER PLANTS (89%); ECOLOGY and ENVIRONMENTAL SCIENCE (89%); ENERGY and UTILITY POLICY (86%); SOLAR ENERGY (86%); TAXES and TAXATION (86%); CLIMATOLOGY (86%); TAX LAW (85%); WIND ENERGY (78%); ENVIRONMENTAL ENGINEERING and CONSULTING (78%); BIOMASS (78%); CREDIT CRISIS (78%); RECESSION (78%); ECONOMIC NEWS (78%); ENERGY EFFICIENCY and CONSERVATION (78%); US ECONOMIC STIMULUS PLAN 2008-2009 (75%); ENVIRONMENTAL IMPACT ASSESSMENT (73%); LEGISLATORS (73%); POLITICAL PARTIES (73%); GLOBAL WARMING (70%); SHAREHOLDER MEETINGS (69%); HYDROELECTRIC POWER (69%); ENERGY RESEARCH (64%); US DEMOCRATIC PARTY (63%); COAL INDUSTRY (50%); CORPORATE TAX (50%); HEDGE FUND