nd may start the project in Cambay basin heavy oil field soon," he added.LiNeBrEaKWe have the technology to transport the carbon dioxide which we would need from thermal power plants to be injected  in the heavy oil fields, he added.		OIL EXTRACTION (91%); GEOLOGY and GEOPHYSICS (89%); OIL and GAS INDUSTRY (89%); EMISSIONS (78%); GLOBAL WARMING (74%); RESEARCH INSTITUTES (73%); ELECTRIC POWER PLANTS (73%); POWER PLANTS (72%); ENVIRONMENT and NATURAL RESOURCES (69%)  	MCCLATCHY-TRIBUNE INFORMATION SERVICES (63%); SINTEF GROUP (53%)  			NEW DELHI, INDIA (90%) INDIA (94%)  	January 16, 2009  	ENGLISH  			Newspaper  	2009 HT Media Ltd.   	Satyen Mohapatra, Hindustan Times, New Delhi  			General  	Distributed by McClatchy-Tribune Business News  	20090116-HJ-NGRI-collaborates-with-Norway-for-extracting-more-oil-using-carbon-dioxide-0116  	HJ  									
