The Salt Lake Tribune 	January 16, 2009 Friday 	Readers writing to Obama, Part 1  	NEWS; State  	3020 words  	Dear Mr. President,LiNeBrEaKThis is a letter I wrote after you were elected president.LiNeBrEaKThe WorldLiNeBrEaKWhere people are rushing and there is no peace.LiNeBrEaKWhere people are fighting, others are crying, sometimes people are dying. The world is falling apart.LiNeBrEaKThe world is also a fantastic place to be.LiNeBrEaKWith its oceans, its beautiful fields of grass, its amazing mountains and sunsets.LiNeBrEaKOur delicious fruits and vegetables. LiNeBrEaKIt truly is a beautiful world.LiNeBrEaKSoon we'll have a new leader - hopefully it will change the world.LiNeBrEaKHope is an amazing thing - it got Barack Obama where he is today.LiNeBrEaKI remember him when I think of hope.LiNeBrEaKWith Peace and Hope - Sincerely,LiNeBrEaKAddy Gesteland (age 8)LiNeBrEaKTo: President-Elect ObamaLiNeBrEaKFrom: Grandpa's Taxi Service LiNeBrEaKSubject: request for financial assistanceLiNeBrEaKSince retiring, I have become known far and wide as Grandpa's Taxi Service (herein known as The Company.) Being a senior citizen on a fixed income, I have been forced to provide service with a somewhat elderly pickup truck. This not acceptable for the quality of passengers served, has very poor fuel economy, is not good for emissions of greenhouse gases and leaves a very ugly CARBON FOOTPRINT.LiNeBrEaKPlease note that as CEO of The Company I provide these special services for a salary of $0. 00 dollars per year. The Company provides no pension plan, no health care and no Golden Parachute. I therefore feel it would be proper to upgrade my fleet. After extensive research, I have determined that the best vehicle for the purpose would be a Cadillac CTS. This would be beneficial in several ways. It would provide the comfort my special passengers are Entitled to, would improve fuel economy, reduce dependence on foreign oil, improve greenhouse gas emissions, help the struggling automakers and greatly improve the CARBON FOOTPRINT.LiNeBrEaKWhile I feel it is totally unconscionable to beg for charity and then use other people's money for a "RETREAT" at an expensive luxury resort, it should be noted that the passengers believe that the proper route from school to home goes through BASKIN ROBBINS, therefore I have added an extra $20. 00 to request, Strictly in the interest of passenger satisfaction.LiNeBrEaKI believe the increased fuel economy will offset the rise in insurance premiums, so you may rest assured I will not be back for more.LiNeBrEaKI therefore respectfully request a BAILOUT in the amount of $93,237. 19.LiNeBrEaKAnxiously waiting;LiNeBrEaKGary MechamLiNeBrEaKWoods Cross, UtahLiNeBrEaKSubject: Too little, too lateLiNeBrEaKAfter losing my job in September, I received a decent severance check. This payment increased our 2008 income quite a bit. Of course, this also increases our taxes. Even though this income is supposed to get us by for several months into 2009, we still have to pay taxes on it on our 2008 return. We usually get a refund each year, but now it looks like we will have to pay this year. I still have not found a job. It's great that we may be receiving some money back later in the year, but how do we come up with the cash to pay what is going to be due when we file our taxes right now? This money due will decrease the monies that we have set aside to keep us going until I am eligible for unemployment. How do we get by then? Do we pull money from our retirement accounts to get us by? Do we use our credit card and dig ourselves deeper into debt? Sure, to most, this is not a lot of money, but to someone who is unemployed, it is a great amount - it has to last until a new job comes along, which may be quite a while. I fear that help will not come soon enough for us - how many more people out there are in the same position, but with less than we have?LiNeBrEaKSandra TomlinsonLiNeBrEaKDear President Obama,LiNeBrEaKThe USA and the world economy is now in deep deep trouble for the time being. As such, it is very nice to see that you seem to be in the top of the issue, beside all the important task of transition. However, please remember, with todays' globalization, magnitude of problem need different approach, and this time around, this seemingly US-triggered economic problem will need your leadership of different paradigm. i.e. it needs World Wide Effort, all the countries in the world, to make a difference!!!!LiNeBrEaKThis world is interdependent world, you have to think, "What does it take to turn around the world economy?"LiNeBrEaKI believe with your talent, leadership, humanity, humility, if you take a world wide leading effort to turn around the economy, it will be a lot easier and it can be done, today's crisis, it's confidence crisis, its contracting in a unprecedented scale, and it will need all the leaders of the top 50 economies to generate an entirely different approach to make a different!LiNeBrEaKThat is the legacy awaiting you, it will not be easy, but Yes we can! Barrack H. Obama, you are destined to call a world wide effort to tackle this economic problem of such a scale and put down your self ego, get Hillary Clinton, Bill Clinton, George W. Bush, George Bush Sr, Jimmy Carter, get the diplomats going, get the world to work together to get a overwhelming responce and then, the whole world will resolve this problem and crisis, together, yes, We can!LiNeBrEaKPlease, please do not solve this problem of USA alone as a nation, this is now a world wide problem, crisis of different dimension! You must think out of box, think out of the nation's border, "What does it take to fix the world economy? " let's sit down with the world leaders, and get the task moving, Yes, We can.LiNeBrEaKThanks and regards,LiNeBrEaKRonnieLiNeBrEaKMr. President Elect Obama,LiNeBrEaKTough times require sacrifices. Just as you and many of us are appalled at the excesses of the Financial, Corporate and Public Sector executives, I cannot believe the costs and the risks of this train trip are at all appropriate even for the President of the United States at this time in our Nation's History.LiNeBrEaKPlease set the correct tone for fiscal responsibility and common sense, for the beginning of your presidency. I view this trip no different than the AIG "Seminars"!LiNeBrEaKI read the Audacity of Hope a year ago. I voted for you because of it. This trip could be viewed as the Audacity of Stupidity.LiNeBrEaKPlease reconsider this reckless and costly self indulging "PERK".LiNeBrEaKRichard R.LiNeBrEaKMr President,LiNeBrEaKWe build the Panama Canal and keep it running with dredging crews, so why don't we spend more time with preventive measures such as dredging so that when heavy rains and snow show up, our infrastructure won't be waterlogged, what to do with the dredged material is use it as fill in, and recycle all the usable things found bikes tires etc., seems simple but why have I heard of no one doing this my any areas that are constantly flooded ?LiNeBrEaKDear Mr. President-Elect,LiNeBrEaKPerhaps the most troubling things we have seen in the past sixteen years is the rapid expansion of presidential powers. One of the changes we desperately need is for this power to be rolled back to the levels outlined in the Constitution. Though it would be tempting to keep these policies in place to aid in the implementation of your agenda, we need to look at the effect this will have on future Presidents. Let us learn from the past, too much power in the hands of a corrupt individual can be devastating for a nation.LiNeBrEaKTwo qualities more than anything else will be required to accomplish the rollback of presidential power: humility and leadership. The founding fathers understood the importance of the system of checks and balances, it will require much humility to admit to yourself that preservation of the overall system is more important than implementation of any particular policy you wish to be in place. This expansion of powers would not have been possible if congress had not allowed their power to be usurped by the past Presidents. The fact that this power was relinquished willingly means you will need to convince the legislative branch to take back the authority and responsibility they have given away.LiNeBrEaKMr. Obama, please exercise the humility and leadership that will be required to take the United States of America into the future within the bounds set forth in the Constitution.LiNeBrEaKSincerely,LiNeBrEaKNick DuclosLiNeBrEaKDear President Obama,LiNeBrEaKI want you to know how much I admire and respect you. I feel confident for the first time in many many years that our country is in good hands. I trust you to help us get back on a rational and stable course, both financially and politically.LiNeBrEaKThe state of Utah is $1 billion dollars in the red because of tax shortfall. If the federal government could give this state the money it needs to recover from this shortfall, we would be able to save thousands of jobs. People would be able to keep their houses. They would be able to spend money from which the state could collect taxes and the federal government would collect substantially more income tax. In addition, there would be less drain on state money because fewer people would be on unemployment and welfare. I teach at a university. I have been there for over 25 years. Now we are hearing that hundreds of jobs will be cut this year. Our neighbor university is cutting 660 jobs. This type of cutting is going to spiral us down into a crisis of enormous severity which will take the government years and years to recover from.LiNeBrEaKIf we could have the money to balance our budget we could go on and the economy would start to recover. I believe the people of this state are willing to go the extra mile and pitch in to help out. If we have hope we can volunteer to work on projects without pay to repay the loan or grant from the federal government. The people of this state are industrious, civic minded people who are willing to work very hard to save the economy of this state and help the nation. We are proud to be American. All we need is hope through financial help, and knowing what we can do. We can organize ourselves if we just know what needs to be done or what can be done. LiNeBrEaKI am very appreciative of this opportunity to write you. May God bless you and keep you and your family happy and healthy.LiNeBrEaKWith respect,LiNeBrEaKGiana CurtisLiNeBrEaKDear President Obama,LiNeBrEaKI am writing to ask that your administration take a strong position against Israel's violation of human rights in Gaza. Through its blockade and shelling of civilian areas, Israel is collectively punishing the Palestinian people for the military tactics of Hamas. Please work to find a diplomatic solution to the fighting in the Middle East - there is no military solution that will lead to peace there.LiNeBrEaKThe other concern I have is that major corporations in the United States are treating the U.S. Treasury as their personal ATM machine. Please use any bailout grants and loans to ensure long-term economic development in the best interest of our country, including preservation of heavy manufacturing ability, construction of 21st century clean transportation networks, solar and wind power, and equal educational opportunity for all regardless of their social and economic class.LiNeBrEaKThank you for your consideration of these ideas.LiNeBrEaKSincerely,LiNeBrEaKRachel WhiteLiNeBrEaKSalt Lake CityLiNeBrEaKDear Mr. PresidentLiNeBrEaKBernard DeVoto once wrote that public lands policy is one of the few areas where our government can make an irretrievable mistake, one that cannot be corrected later on. Please do everything in your power to save our dwindling wildlands from degradation. Once lost, they are gone for generations, if not forever.LiNeBrEaKPresident Bush, catering to the "drill baby drill" crowd, made oil and gas leasing the top priority for the Bureau of Land Management. This was yet another example of his malfeasance, part of the worst presidency in our history. These leases cannot be undone, but immediate action is needed to reverse direction. The first step should be to order a moratorium on further leasing until land management plans can be rewritten to place roadless areas off limits. This will not affect the nation's oil supply because of the enormous backlog of undrilled leases. Also, require the BLM to place no-surface-occupancy stipulations on all drilling permits for leases in environmentally sensitive areas.LiNeBrEaKLast month, Tim DeChristopher courageously took nonviolent direct action to save some of Utah's wilderness-quality BLM lands from the Bush administration's final, and most disastrous, oil and gas auction. Mr. DeChristopher did the right thing, while our government was abusing its power to do the wrong thing. If he is charged with a crime, please issue an immediate presidential pardon. Thank you.LiNeBrEaKLike most Americans, I am very grateful that we finally have a new President and a new Congress dedicated to restoring peace and prosperity in America and the world. I wish you luck, and if you need help just ask. We'll be there for you.LiNeBrEaKSincerely,LiNeBrEaKRichard M. WarnickLiNeBrEaKDraper, UtahLiNeBrEaKI am only one of thousands that depend on our SSDI's. It hurts when a office of the government treats you like a plague.LiNeBrEaKI got my SSDI dropped because of selling a house in 2007. The house wasn't even mine but my guardian's. When she passed away I had to sell the house for her children. Most of the money went to pay off the mortgage. The money it left was divided between her two girls but Social Security in California would not listen to my reason. Why can't the government give us a break?LiNeBrEaKDaisy JonesLiNeBrEaKMr. President. . .LiNeBrEaKI am one of your loyal supporters. And I ask now for your help. Here in Utah, we have a man serving a 55-year sentence for selling a not large amount of marijuana. If ever there were an unjust sentence, this is one.LiNeBrEaKUnderstanding the enormous pressures of your position, I still must beg you to help this man. You are the only one who can. His name is Weldon Angelos.LiNeBrEaKGod bless you Mr. President.LiNeBrEaKSincerely,LiNeBrEaKKeith Colledge, SLC, UT.LiNeBrEaKDear Mr. President,LiNeBrEaKIn the movie "Forrest Gump," one of the most memorable lines was, "I'm not a smart man." As it turned out he was a very smart man. He surrounded himself with smart people, he watched over and cared for the people in his life and he made a huge difference in the world. I realize this movie is Hollywood at its best and yet if we examine the movie, much can be learned.LiNeBrEaKMy husband is among the 16% of Americans who have lost their jobs. He is a trainer, has trained in many countries, and yet he lost his job. Why? If companies aren't growing, they aren't hiring, thus no need for a trainer. Lane is extremely wise, he has an amazing intellect. In the evening after searching for a job he will spend hours on the computer filling out applications all over the world. We need to find him a job. Putting the economy back into Americans' hands is critical. I realize you have many projects, so if along the way you need someone with an amazing intellect, please consider my husband.LiNeBrEaKBlessings,LiNeBrEaKCindy WinwardLiNeBrEaKSalt Lake City, UtahLiNeBrEaKDear Mr. President-elect:LiNeBrEaKTo simply say "congratulations" is almost inane, however, if that is how literally changing history; reversing the old "it can't be done" mind-set, and developing a workable system (perhaps in the first time of the U.S. history) is defined, so be it.LiNeBrEaKBest wishes for the times ahead,LiNeBrEaKGeorge Novak - voter.LiNeBrEaKDear Mr. President,LiNeBrEaKArticle 2, Section 1 of the Constitution that you are going to swear and oath the support and defend says that "only a natural-born citizen" may be President. I urge you to come clean about your birth status. You say you were born in Hawaii but your grandmother says you were born in Kenya to a Kenyan father and an underage mother. Why have you hired three law firms to conceal your college records? Why won't you provide a valid birth certificate? Why do your Indonesian school records show your name as Barry Soetoro? How were you able to travel to Pakistan in 1981 when it was illegal at the time for American citizens to travel there?LiNeBrEaKHow were you able to enroll in school in Indonesia when only Indonesian citizens are allowed to go to school there? If you won't even follow this simple portion of the Constitution now then what is there to make the American people believe that you will abide by the oath of office you will be taking? It is my belief sir that you do not meet the "natural-born" requirement and that is why you are doing everything in your power to conceal that fact and unfortunately you appear to be a fraud. Please step down or show the proof that you indeed meet the requirement of being "natural born" as required by the Constitution of which you are supposed to be committed to uphold.LiNeBrEaKSincerely,LiNeBrEaKJJ SurpriseLiNeBrEaKSandy, UtahLiNeBrEaKDear Mr. PresidentLiNeBrEaKFirst off, Congratulations to our new President. You have my 100% support. Take your time on many new and important issues and America will once again prosper and be respected in the world. I am retired after 21 years in the US Army and teaching JROTC at East High School for 21 years. Not bad for an immigrant that came to Utah at age 21 from Germany. I have a recommendation for a stimulus for Seniors.LiNeBrEaKAllow us to withdraw $ 10,000. 00 from our IRA, my wife's and mine, with a 10% tax . That would cost me $ 1000. 00, but do not tax that amount with my annual tax statement. Our combined income is about $ 53,000. 00, withdrawing $ 10,000. 00 would cost me an additional $2,500. 00 to $ 3,000. 00. Allowing this stimulus would not cost the government much, but give seniors a break and they could make needed purchases or pay bills.LiNeBrEaKSecond, when giving large amounts of our taxpayer money to bail out companies , put a restriction on its use that would restrict CEOs using that money for their large pay and bonuses. After all, these managers have mismanaged their company and are partially at fault for the trouble the economy is in.LiNeBrEaKAgain, I give you my support and thank you for the unbelievable job you have ahead of you. May god give you the strength and courage to do what is ahead of us.LiNeBrEaKSincerelyLiNeBrEaKHenry L. Vogel.LiNeBrEaKDear Mr. President:LiNeBrEaKIt would help the Seniors If we would eliminate or reduce the taxing of Social Security, State and Federal retirement income for retired persons 65 or older or at certain income levels.LiNeBrEaKSincerelyLiNeBrEaKL E. Staley/ DJ StaleyLiNeBrEaKDear President Obama -LiNeBrEaKWhy not mandate that all ARM mortgages revert to their teaser rates? Presumably, the homeowners could afford those terms, and it might result in many fewer foreclosures.LiNeBrEaKI wish you luck in your new office and will pray for you.LiNeBrEaKSincerely,LiNeBrEaKLisa WeissLiNeBrEaKTampa, FL		PRESIDENTIAL ELECTIONS (90%); EMISSIONS (87%); CARBON OFFSETS (87%); CLIMATE CHANGE (77%); TAXICABS and LIMOUSINES (73%); MOTOR VEHICLES (72%); PENSION and RETIREMENT PLANS (72%); WAGES and SALARIES (72%); AUTOMAKERS (72%); SEVERANCE PAY (70%); TAXES and TAXATION (67%); AUTOMOTIVE MFG (66%); AUTOMOBILE MFG (64%); ENERGY and UTILITY POLICY (64%); INSURANCE PREMIUMS (50%); US PRESIDENTS (78%); SENIOR CITIZENS (73%)  			BARACK OBAMA (94%)  		January 21, 2009  	ENGLISH  			Newspaper  	2009 The Salt Lake Tribune All Rights Reserved  	The Salt Lake Tribune  															
San Gabriel Valley Tribune (California) 	January 16, 2009 Friday 	Winds have changed at ports  	OPINION  	546 words  	Hard numbers are replacing good intentions and hopeful optimism. The facts are in, and the results are clear: The air downwind of Long Beach and Los Angeles is safer to breathe. LiNeBrEaKA study released this week shows declines in five of eight categories of pollutants from activity at the Port of Long Beach. The Port of L.A. reported similar improvements in December. The air quality is getting better, and it looks like the next batch of numbers should be even better.LiNeBrEaKHere's the most important result: Diesel emissions are down 21 percent. These are the nasty by-products of diesel-powered ships, trucks, trains and equipment responsible for higher rates of cancer, heart disease and asthma in neighborhoods near the ports.LiNeBrEaKHere's another: Sulfur oxides are down even more sharply: 36 percent. These are the pollutants that, when combined with the natural moisture of our lungs, turn into sulfuric acid. Sulfate particulates also are not good for the lungs.LiNeBrEaKThe efforts of the two ports have made a huge difference. For example, the dirtiest trucks on the road, those built in 1988 or before, no longer are allowed at the Port of Long Beach, and the L.A. port has less effective but similar restrictions. Bob Kanter, director of environmental planning at the Long Beach port, says the main reasons for success with the reductions of sulfur have been the slowing of ship 20 miles of port, and the use of low-sulfur fuel.LiNeBrEaKThe Long Beach port paid $1 million in incentives to encourage the slower ship speeds, but the use of low-sulfur fuels makes a different point. Federal regulations mandated cutting sulfur in diesel fuel from 500 parts per million to 15 parts, and state regulations adopted the same rules for ships, although the state's efforts got overruled by a federal judge. (Many shippers have continued to use low-sulfur fuel thanks to port financial incentives.)LiNeBrEaKThe lesson is that the ports alone can make a huge difference in cleaning up pollution, but it takes federal and state regulation to do the complete job. The two ports are the biggest single source of diesel pollution in Southern California, but overall, they are responsible for just 20 percent of it. There are thousands more trucks, buses and trains to clean up.LiNeBrEaKTwo categories of emissions have increased. Nitrogen oxides, an ingredient of smog, rose slightly, from 16,720 tons to 16,923 tons, and carbon dioxide has gone up 7 percent. Carbon dioxide isn't toxic (we mammals exhale it with every breath and trees depend on it) but it is an ingredient in the atmospheric canopy related to global warming.LiNeBrEaKThere is a related issue. Shipping volume has declined recently along with the general economy, and some economists speculate that because of long-term changes in consumer behavior and increased competition from other ports, some of that business may not come back. This might lessen future problems, but it doesn't change the fact that the poisonous by-products of transporting goods must be cleaned up locally. The ports deserve credit for taking this on.LiNeBrEaKBut the statewide, national and global challenges remain, and will take not just the continually sidetracked efforts of state agencies, but a change of attitude by the federal government. For those solutions, we should look to the new administration.		EDITORIALS and OPINIONS (90%); EMISSIONS (89%); DIESEL FUEL (89%); VEHICLE EMISSIONS (89%); PARTICULATE MATTER (78%); AIR POLLUTION (78%); AIR QUALITY (78%); RESEARCH REPORTS (78%); SMOG (77%); CONSUMER BEHAVIOR (77%); AIR QUALITY REGULATION (76%); GLOBAL WARMING (75%); ASTHMA (72%); VEHICLE TRAFFIC (69%); DISEASES and DISORDERS (69%); MAMMALS (68%)  				LOS ANGELES, CA, USA (93%) CALIFORNIA, USA (93%) UNITED STATES (93%)  	January 18, 2009  	ENGLISH  			Newspaper  	2009 MediaNews Group, Inc. and Los Angeles Newspap