self off dependence on foreign oil despite the wide fluctuations in gasoline prices during the past year. While gas prices are currently around $1. 75 a gallon, Mr. Rendell predicted that gasoline prices will reach $3 a gallon by summer.LiNeBrEaKMr. Rendell said applicants can start applying in March and April for state aid to help finance wind and geothermal projects.LiNeBrEaKIn Northeast Pennsylvania, wind turbines are located along the ridges at several locations, while the trillions of gallons of water in abandoned anthracite mines are being eyed as a potential geothermal source to heat or cool buildings.LiNeBrEaKThe guidelines approved by the Commonwealth Financing Authority set $5 million as the maximum loan and $1 million as the maximum grant for projects.LiNeBrEaKApplicants are to estimate the number of jobs created, how the project will reduce the state's reliance on conventional energy sources and potential environmental benefits such as the tons of air emissions from greenhouse gases that could be avoided.LiNeBrEaKThe funds can be used to buy land and buildings, build or renovate buildings and purchase and install equipment.LiNeBrEaKThe state has yet to enter the bond market to sell energy bonds to investors.LiNeBrEaKContact the writer: rswift@timesshamrock.com		ENERGY DEVELOPMENT PROGRAMS (92%); BIOFUELS (92%); AUTOMOTIVE FUELS (90%); RENEWABLE ENERGY (90%); ELECTRIC POWER PLANTS (90%); GEOTHERMAL ENERGY (89%); ENERGY and ENVIRONMENT (89%); OIL and GAS PRICES (89%); GRANTS and GIFTS (89%); WIND POWER PLANTS (89%); POWER and COMMUNICATION SYSTEM CONSTRUCTION (89%); WIND ENERGY (89%); GASOLINE PRICES (88%); BONDS (87%); POWER PLANTS (78%); EMISSIONS (78%); NATURAL GAS and ELECTRIC UTILITIES (78%); ENERGY and UTILITY CONSTRUCTION (78%); APPROVALS (78%); ENERGY and UTILITY POLICY (78%); GOVERNORS (78%); US STATE GOVERNMENT (78%); APPROPRIATIONS (78%); DIESEL FUEL (75%); CLIMATE CHANGE (75%); ALTERNATIVE FUEL PROGRAMS (75%); BOND MARKETS (72%); FOSSIL FUEL PO