t warm.LiNeBrEaKAnd yeah, I've got to admit, I've lived through some bad winters since I've been in Owensboro.LiNeBrEaKWho can forget Jan. 19, 1994, when the mercury plunged all the way to a record 23 degrees below zero?LiNeBrEaKHeck, it never even got above zero on Jan. 18 and only climbed to 10 degrees above on the 19th.LiNeBrEaKThen, there was the 19 below on Jan. 20, 1989. And the 17 below on Jan. 11, 1977.LiNeBrEaKHeck, the winter of '77 saw 11 days with below zero temperatures in January -- and five of them were 10 degrees or more below zero.LiNeBrEaKI'm still shivering from that one.LiNeBrEaKScientists say global temperatures will remain about the same until 2015 and then begin to rise.LiNeBrEaKHallelujah!LiNeBrEaKOn Jan. 15, 1998, -- 11 years ago today -- I wrote these words: "I was driving home Monday, just before dark. It was 55 degrees. My heater was turned off. Heck, I was thinking about rolling down the window.LiNeBrEaK"Joggers were everywhere, running alone and in packs. And most of them were wearing shorts and sleeveless shirts.LiNeBrEaK"So far this month, the only high less than 40 degrees was Tuesday's 34. Before that, 42 degrees last Saturday had been our coldest high.LiNeBrEaK"Shoot, we've hit 66 twice already this month. Four days have been in the 60s. Four more were in the 50s. And the rest have been in the 40s.LiNeBrEaK"My gosh, we've had five lows in the 50s this month -- including a 59 on Jan. 6.LiNeBrEaK"And the coldest we've seen so far has been 25 degrees."LiNeBrEaKWhat a heavenly winter!LiNeBrEaKBut this winter, the National Weather Service says the U.S. saw more than 2,000 daily snowfall records in December.LiNeBrEaKAnd 6. 8 million square miles of American soil was covered by snow last month.LiNeBrEaKFortunately, none of them was around here.LiNeBrEaKA January day without snow is a day to be treasured.LiNeBrEaKEven if it is cold enough to freeze the jaws off a brass monkey.		CLIMATOLOGY (91%); GLOBAL WARMING (91%); SCIENCE NEWS (89%); S