The Pittsburgh Tribune-Review (Pennsylvania)  	January 15, 2009 Thursday 	EDITORIAL: The Thursday wrap  	COMMENTARY  	310 words  	Jan. 15--Stuff 'em: You might recall that five of the pirates who were paid $3 million to release a Saudi oil tanker drowned last week as they made their escape. Well, at least one of the bodies washed ashore on the coast of Somalia with more than $150,000 in cash on his person. Might we make a suggestion (other than to stop negotiating with pirates)? The body of this pirate and any others recovered should be stuffed and each one mounted on the bow of a supertanker. LiNeBrEaKUnsettled science: Uh-oh. Peer-reviewed science has just thrown some more sand into the gears of the Carbon Commandos' theory of global warming. A Danish study published this week in the Videnskab and Geology journals suggests the relationship between the Earth's magnetic field and galactic cosmic ray particles -- not human emissions -- is responsible for climate change. Yet another indication that the "settled science" of global warming is not.LiNeBrEaKAnd they're off!: Former state Revenue Secretary Tom Wolf has become the first candidate to announce for Pennsylvania governor for 2010. Mr. Wolf, a Democrat, will be able to mount a well-funded campaign, given his personal wealth from a business supply company. No fewer than four other Democrats and four Republicans are weighing a run to replace Ed Rendell, who's constitutionally barred from seeking a third four-year term. Ah, a 16-month gubernatorial primary race. We're fatigued already.		EDITORIALS and OPINIONS (91%); POLITICAL PARTIES (90%); EMISSIONS (78%); RESEARCH REPORTS (75%); GLOBAL WARMING (74%); CLIMATE CHANGE (74%); WEALTHY PEOPLE (73%); GOVERNORS (72%); CAMPAIGNS and ELECTIONS (71%); US DEMOCRATIC PARTY (71%); US REPUBLICAN PARTY (71%); GEOLOGY and GEOPHYSICS (70%); PRIMARY ELECTIONS (66%)  	MCCLATCHY-TRIBUNE INFORMATION SERVICES (82%)  		ED RENDELL (54%)  	PENNSYLVANIA, USA (92%); EARTH (79%) UNITED STAT