f Gulf Coast states to take greater heed of climate-change warnings. The Gulf of Mexico Alliance is a government collaborative focused on protecting the Gulf of Mexico. It includes Florida, Alabama, Louisiana, Mississippi and Texas. Climate change activists like the Gulf Coast Restoration Network and the Southern Alliance for Clean Energy say the alliance needs to make climate change a priority. "We need our leaders to love our coast and the gulf as much as we do and protect our resources from their greatest threat: global warming," said Joe Murphy, an activist with the Gulf Restoration Network.LiNeBrEaKFor WTSP workers, a week with no payLiNeBrEaKEmployees of WTSP-Ch. 10 will take a week of unpaid leave before April in a cost-cutting measure aimed to avoid layoffs. Gannett Co., the station's owner as well as publisher of USA Today and numerous other newspapers, announced the companywide measure Wednesday. Channel 10 employs about 175 people, records show. Gannett spokeswoman Tara Connell said many on-air reporters have individual contracts with the station and cannot be required to take leave.		AIRPORTS (93%); CREDIT CRISIS (90%); CLIMATE CHANGE (89%); COASTAL AREAS (86%); INVENTORIES (77%); BANKING and FINANCE (74%); BAILOUTS (74%); ECONOMIC NEWS (73%); ECONOMIC SURVEYS (73%); AUTOMOTIVE SALES (72%); OIL and GAS PRICES (72%); RETAILERS (72%); EMPLOYEE LEAVE (69%); ENVIRONMENTALISM (64%); NEWSPAPER PUBLISHING (63%); ENVIRONMENT and NATURAL RESOURCES (63%); GLOBAL WARMING (62%); LAYOFFS (60%)  	GANNETT CO INC (81%); ALLEGIANT TRAVEL CO (57%)  			TAMPA, FL, USA (92%); ATLANTA, GA, USA (79%) FLORIDA, USA (93%); ATLANTIC OCEAN (92%); GULF OF MEXICO (92%); SOUTHEAST USA (92%); LOUISIANA, USA (79%); MISSISSIPPI, USA (79%); GEORGIA, USA (79%); ALABAMA, USA (79%); TEXAS, USA (79%) UNITED STATES (94%); NORTH AMERICA (92%)  	January 15, 2009  	ENGLISH  			Newspaper  	2009 Times Publishing Company All Rights Reserved  			GCI (NYSE) (81%); ALGT (NASDAQ) (57%)  	NAICS511110 NEW