 in global warming and in the wars that we are currently fighting.LiNeBrEaKWhen I was a boy, we had one war at a time and that way we tended to win -- without surges and stuff like that.LiNeBrEaKAnd I hope that somebody will apologize to all those mothers who used to ruin their eyes by sewing new Barbie outfits -- sequins and all.LiNeBrEaKAnd I hope that Barbie will admit that she is too old to be a doll anymore.LiNeBrEaKBoy, I hope this satire was slashing.		TOYS and GAMES MFG (90%); DOLL and STUFFED TOY MFG (90%); TOYS and GAMES (90%); PHYSICIANS and SURGEONS (76%); MOTOR VEHICLES (50%); GLOBAL WARMING (50%)  	MATTEL INC (95%)  				January 17, 2009  	ENGLISH  			Newspaper  	2009 The Roanoke Times All Rights Reserved  	BEN BEAGLE  		MAT (NYSE) (95%)  	NAICS339932 GAME, TOY and CHILDREN'S VEHICLE MANUFACTURING (95%); NAICS339931 DOLL and STUFFED TOY MANUFACTURING (95%); SIC3944 GAMES, TOYS, and CHILDREN'S VEHICLES, EXCEPT DOLLS and BICYCLES (95%); SIC3942 DOLLS and STUFFED TOYS (95%)  												
San Jose Mercury News (California)  	January 12, 2009 Monday 	Yeager appointed to California Air Resources Board  	STATE AND REGIONAL NEWS  	356 words  	Jan. 12--Gov. Arnold Schwarzenegger has appointed Santa Clara County Supervisor Ken Yeager to the California Air Resources Board. Yeager, 56, of San Jose, has served as a county supervisor since December 2006. LiNeBrEaKThe air board is among the most powerful agencies in the state. With 11 members appointed by the governor, it sets pollution rules on a wide variety of issues, including diesel regulation, auto emissions standards, gasoline chemistry and most recently, global warming regulation. Members receive travel expenses, but no salary, and must be confirmed by the state Senate.LiNeBrEaKEstablished in 1967, the board has often set regulations that have been adopted by other states and the nation, including banning leaded gasoline, requiring the first auto engine standards and other measures.LiNeBrEaKYeager is a member of the Bay Area Air Quality Management District, the Association of Bay Area Governments, the California State Association of Counties Climate Change Task Force, the Santa Clara County Health Authority, the Valley Transportation Authority and the Metropolitan Transportation Commission.LiNeBrEaKAn avid triathlete and environmentalist, he previously served on the San Jose City Council from 2001 to 2006, and before that taught political science at San Jose State University. Yeager, a Democrat and former press secretary to U.S. Rep. Don Edwards, holds a bachelor's degree in political science from San Jose State, and a Master's and PhD in education from StanfordLiNeBrEaKUniversity.LiNeBrEaKOn the board of supervisors, Yeager represents the 4th District, which includes the cities of Campbell and Santa Clara, as well as west San Jose and the Cambrian neighborhood.LiNeBrEaKContact Paul Rogers at progers@mercurynews.com or (408) 920-5045.		COUNTY GOVERNMENT (91%); AIR QUALITY (90%); LEGISLATIVE BODIES (90%)